# Git & README Discipline

## Commit Format (Conventional Commits)

```
type(scope): short imperative description

Optional body explaining why.
```

**Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `test`, `refactor`, `docs`, `chore`, `security`

**Examples:**
```
feat(ledger): add optimistic locking on Account entity
test(market): add unit tests for price-time priority matcher
docs: update README with ledger API examples
chore(infra): add docker-compose with kafka and postgres
```

## Commit Rules

- **One logical change per commit** (target ≤200 LOC diff).
- Commit **before** starting the next feature or module.
- Never commit: `.env`, keys, passwords, `application-local.*`.
- Never use `--no-verify` unless the user explicitly requests it.

## README Sync (required before push)

Update [README.md](../../README.md) when any of these change:

- New module or service
- New environment variable
- New API endpoint or Kafka topic
- Architecture or quick-start steps
- Milestone completed (check roadmap section)

If code changed but README did not need an update, say so in the commit message body.

## Branching

- `main` — stable, always deployable
- Feature branches: `feat/m0c-spring-skeleton`, `feat/ledger-transfers`
- One branch per milestone or feature; merge to `main` when tests pass
